making a quick buck means finding ways to earn money quickly and efficiently. Here are some methods that could work for different circumstances:

1. Selling items you no longer need: if you have old books, gadgets, or clothes lying around, selling them at a thrift store or using online marketplaces like eBay, Craigslist, or Facebook Marketplace can net you some extra cash.

2. Offering services in demand: depending on your skills, you might offer private tutoring in subjects like mathematics, language, test preparation;
